This is a stand-alone application for the CRAMS NeCTAR provisioning

Getting Started
---------------

Set up a virtualenv and create py35 virtualenv

# Install python3.5

# Run flake8

tox -e flake8

# Run test

tox -e py35

* Copy local_settings.py.example to local_settings.py
* Modify it to point a desired keystone server and crams api server.

Start CRAMS NeCTAR Provision
----------------------------

# To show the help message:

python crams_provision/provision.py --help

# To list all approved allocation requests ids:

python crams_provision/provision.py --list

# To provision a single allocation request

python crams_provision/provision.py id

# To provision all allocation requests

python crams_provision/provision.py







